The Benue State Governor, Samuel Ortom has felicitated with all Muslims in the State and other parts of the country as Eid-El-Maulud is celebrated today. The Governor assured the people of the state that his administration will continue to collaborate with security agencies to guarantee the safety of lives and property. He appreciates Benue people and other Nigerians for the support given to his administration to surmount the security challenges which confronted the state especially in 2018. Governor Ortom reaffirmed the commitment of the present administration towards the creation of numerous economic opportunities for the people. The Governor enjoined Muslims to seize the opportunity presented by Eid-El-Maulud to pray for peace and unity of Benue State and Nigeria at large as they celebrate the birth of Prophet Mohammed. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.